#: ../../source/websockets/pipes.rst:2
msgid "Pipes"
msgstr "管道"

#: ../../source/websockets/pipes.rst:4
msgid ""
"There is no difference between web sockets **pipes** and the `regular "
"pipes </pipes>`__. The only thing you should be aware of is that instead "
"of throwing ``HttpException``, you should use the ``WsException``. "
"Besides, all pipes will be applied only to the ``data`` parameter "
"(because either validating or transforming ``client`` instance sounds "
"awkward)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/websockets/pipes.rst:11
msgid ""
"info **Hint** The ``WsException`` class is exposed from "
"``@nestjs/websockets`` package."
msgstr ""

